Basic.html#Rat\">ℚ</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"The Bernoulli numbers:\nthe $n$-th Bernoulli number $B_n$ is defined recursively via\n$$B_n = 1 - \\sum_{k < n} \\binom{n}{k}\\frac{B_k}{n+1-k}$$ ","docLink":"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/Bernoulli.html#bernoulli'","kind":"def","line":64,"name":"bernoulli'","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/NumberTheory/Bernoulli.lean#L64-L68"}}],"imports":["Init","Mathlib.Algebra.BigOperators.Field","Mathlib.RingTheory.PowerSeries.Inverse","Mathlib.RingTheory.PowerSeries.Exp"],"instances":[],"name":"Mathlib.NumberTheory.Bernoulli"}